thorities in the cities of Nisibis and Harran. The Life is analyzed from historical and literary perspectives, and its material context is explored by recourse to the latest archaeological surveys and excavations in the region where Simeon lived and worked. The book also follows Simeon as he was transformed into a champion of West Syrian Christianity by later members of that community, who portrayed him as engaging in amicable debates with the intellectually curious caliph al-Ma'mun (813-33) and leading Muslim theologians at his court.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aChristian saintszTurkeyzṬur ʻAbdinvBiography. 0aChristian saintszTurkeyzṬur ʿAbdinvBiography. 0aChristian saintszTurkeyzṬur ʻAbdinvBiography. 0aMonophysiteszTurkeyzṬur ʻAbdinvBiography. 0aMonophysiteszTurkeyzṬur ʿAbdinvBiography. 0aMonophysiteszTurkeyzṬur ʻAbdinvBiography. 4aChristianity. 4aLiterature. 4aReligion. 7aRELIGION / Christianity / Literature & the Arts.2bisacsh1 aBrock, Sebastian, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aBrunner, Kyle, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHoyland, Robert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTannous, Jack, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2021 Part 2z978311074335708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertGorgias Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311074330240uhttps://doi.org/10.31826/978146324347040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781463243470423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781463243470/original  a978-3-11-074330-2  Gorgias Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-074335-7  DG Plus PP Package 2021 Part 2b2021  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEB